          {
            "commit": "3f92b85d0db612517bb473212fa15fe967539f88",
            "subject": "LU-6798 kernel: kernel update [SLES11 SP3 3.0.101-0.47.55]"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Frank Zago",
          "email": "fzago@cray.com",
          "date": "2015-08-12 16:44:24.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-09-19 03:33:28.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6995 osd: fix invalid use of bvec_iter_page",
        "message": "LU-6995 osd: fix invalid use of bvec_iter_page\n\nbvec_iter_page is expecting a biovecs list as a first argument, not a\nbiovec. That works as long as there is only one biovec in the bio. If\nthere is more than one, then invalid memory is dereferences since bvl\nis a single vector, not a list. This only affect 3.14+ kernels, where\nHAVE_BVEC_ITER is true. Don't use bvec_iter_page, but create the right\nmacro to simply return the vector's bv_page. Bug introduced in commit\n833b670a.\n\nSigned-off-by: frank zago <fzago@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I390b527bacae9dd650814bb19ab2dbc9184a605d\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/15967\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
